      "span_text": "People who do not know what they do not know tend to think that they almost know all there is to know.  essentially argued that lack of knowledge produces some sort of vicious cycle; one cannot measure accurately his/her level of knowledge without accumulating sufficient knowledge, but the very lack of knowledge hinders people from realizing that they know so little.",
